1.1 Describing the purpose of IT in modern business

In business today, IT or Information and Communications Technology (ICT) is used
to securely communicate, collaborate and streamline the work of staff in the
pursuit of commerce with clients or customers.[1]

[Could list some of the technologies here and state how it allows an organisation
to work as if everyone were sitting in the same office around a large roundtable]

References:
[1] https://www.oksbdc.org/why-is-technology-important-in-business/
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.2 Describing methods, skills and resources needed to complete digital projects
successfully, what do you need to make projects successful? What tools? What skills?

A collaborative endeavour to accomplish a digital project hinges around good
project management, leadership/communication skills and technology.[1]

Version Control Systems such as Git & Github, allow workers to share a codebase,
divide labour into smaller units to work on separately, avoid collisions with other
workers who might try and work on the same file, and track the iterations of the
project. This allows code to be experimented on, rolled back to previous versions,
or for new versions to be developed and tested, and when ready merged into a new
and improved version ready for release.[2]

Kanban, or 'visual cards' software such as Trello can allow teams to collaboratively
perform the role of a digital project manager, in a distributed way.
Workers can plan and then adjust the plan as new tasks are identified and
unforeseen tasks become apparent. Progress can be tracked and the speed of tasks
progress be visible by all, helping to identify and defeat bottlenecks in the
project before deadlines arrive.[3]

These tools facilitate communication across desks, departments and offices, 
to enable even the smallest parts of an organisation in being seen and heard
for their valuable contributions to overall strategy and workflow.

References:
[1] https://www.workamajig.com/blog/digital-project-manager
[2] https://codeburst.io/git-and-github-in-a-nutshell-b0a3cc06458f
[3] https://zapier.com/learn/project-management/kanban-board/
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.3 Plan and carry out tasks using IT – e.g. making your website. How will you
plan it? Include a link to your troll board.

The site will be planned with Trello, using my Board[1], i will have 3 Lists,
that break up the project into 3 stages; 'To Do', 'Doing' and 'Done', and each
will be populated with many Cards, initially to the left side of the Board and
eventually being moved to the right side of the board as work is completed.[2]
References:
[1] my Board link
[2] https://www.industrialmarketer.com/why-i-love-trello-for-business/
